gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Bulls 108, 76ers 104
gameRecap.excerpt: Despite Joel Embiids 40 points, 14 rebounds and six assists, the 76ers fell to the Bulls, 108-104. Coby White recorded 24 points, eight rebounds and nine assists for the Bulls, while Nikola Vucevic added 23 points and eight rebounds in the victory. Tyrese Maxey tallied 29 points, eight assists and five 3PM for the 76ers in the losing effort. The Bulls improve to 11-17 on the season, while the 76ers fall to 18-8, snapping their six-game win streak.
